        "level": "h2"
      },
      "text": "React Context",
      "level": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "React Context is a way to manage state globally.",
      "html": "<p>React Context is a way to manage state globally.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "It can be used together with the useState Hook to share state between deeply nested components more easily than with useState alone.",
      "html": "<p>It can be used together with the <code>useState</code> Hook to share state between\ndeeply nested components more easily than with <code>useState</code> alone.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "metadata": {
        "level": "h2"
      },
      "text": "The Problem",
      "level": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "State should be held by the highest parent component in the stack that requires access to the state.",
      "html": "<p>State should be held by the highest parent component in the stack that requires access to the state.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "To illustrate, we have many nested components. The component at the top and bottom of the stack need access to the state.",
      "html": "<p>To illustrate, we have many nested components. The component at the top and bottom of the stack need access to the state.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "To do this without Context, we will need to pass the state as \"props\" through each nested component. This is called \"prop drilling\".",
      "html": "<p>To do this without Context, we will need to pass the state as \"props\" through each nested component. This is called \"prop drilling\".</p>"
    },
